            <title>[DOXIA-379] Regression: title block isn&apos;t parsed in APT file if comment is present before it</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DOXIA-379</link>
                <project id="12317230" key="DOXIA">Maven Doxia (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently updated to maven-site-plugin-2.1 (which pulled doxia-1.1.2) and suddenly page&lt;br/&gt;
title block stopped working.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My apt file &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; (didn&apos;t change it) now renders as &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;2&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Notice no page title and ugly &quot;------ About ------ Marat Radchenko ------ 2009-04-09&quot; line at top of page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Page starts to render correctly if title block is but before commented license banner, so it becomes a first element.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://autodao.git.sourceforge.net/git/gitweb.cgi?p=autodao/autodao;a=blob;f=src/site/apt/index.apt;h=cda99c5a0500b657162c2ac7f6419df334c41771;hb=HEAD#l17&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://autodao.git.sourceforge.net/git/gitweb.cgi?p=autodao/autodao;a=blob;f=src/site/apt/index.apt;h=cda99c5a0500b657162c2ac7f6419df334c41771;hb=HEAD#l17&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
